  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>lemongrass</strong>, <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half and scrape the seeds out with a spoon</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, reserving some leaves for garnish</p><p>Add the<strong> ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>,<strong> half </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>red chilli</strong> (save the rest for later) and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Once the shallot has softened, add the<strong> beef strips</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong> to the pan with the beef and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>coconut cream</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, add the<strong> fish sauce</strong> with the<strong> lime leaves</strong>, the <strong>juice</strong> of <strong>1/2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lime</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>fragrant stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> and <strong>fragrant stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 4 min or until the beef is cooked through and the sauce has thickened</p><p>Tip: Add an extra splash of water if the sauce thickens too quickly!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the beef is cooking, cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into wedges</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-beef-curry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Thai green beef curry</strong> over the <strong>cooked lemongrass rice</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>coriander leaves</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
